cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it deals with the expressiveness of neural networks. The use of rectified linear units (ReLUs) suggests that it could also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper's focus on activation patterns and probabilistic inference suggests that it could also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of empirical bounds and algorithms for counting solutions suggests that it could also belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
